# SEO Rules

## Metadata
Every page must export `generateMetadata()` sourcing WordPress SEO fields.

```typescript
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const data = await getContent(slug);
  return {
    title: data.seo.title || `${data.title} | Care Well Medical Centre`,
    description: data.seo.description,
    alternates: { canonical: data.seo.canonicalUrl },
    openGraph: { title, description, images, type: 'website' },
    twitter: { card: 'summary_large_image' },
  };
}
```

## Schema (JSON-LD)
- All pages: Organization + BreadcrumbList
- Home: MedicalBusiness | Service: MedicalProcedure | Blog: BlogPosting | Doctors: Physician

## Sitemap & Robots
- `app/sitemap.ts` — dynamic, fetches all slugs from WordPress
- `app/robots.ts` — allow crawlers, point to sitemap

## Rules
- Preserve WordPress slugs exactly — no URL changes without 301 redirects
- Set `metadataBase` in root layout
- One `<h1>` per page with primary keyword
